    • getMajorityClass

      public int getMajorityClass(int attr)
      Returns the majority class for a given attribute. If m_Thresholds are not defined, we return the majority class (equivalent to threshold = 0.5), otherwise, it is currently guaranteed that this is MLC-case, and the label is considered relevant if P(label) >= threshold. Usually, this can be computed as

      m_ClassCounts[attr][0] / m_SumWeights[attr]

      but in voting procedure (see, e.g. voteProbDistr(ArrayList), the counts are normalized whereas the sums of weights are not, hence, the label is considered relevant IFF

      clcts[0] / (clcts[0] + clcts[1]) >= m_Thresholds[attr]

      Parameters:
      attr - Index of the attribute, whose majority class is returned.
      Returns:
      The index that corresponds to the value of majority class.
